President Joe Biden has appointed Alaina B. Teplitz as Assistant Secretary of State for Administration. Teplitz is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has served as Ambassador to Sri Lanka and Maldives since 2018. She has also served as U.S. Ambassador to Nepal from 2015-2018. Teplitz joined the State Department in 1991 and has received numerous Superior and Meritorious Honor Awards. She has held various positions focused on improving diplomacy and reforming the bureaucracy. Her previous assignments include U.S. Embassy Kabul, the State Department's Foreign Service Institute, and various diplomatic missions around the world. Teplitz holds a Bachelor of Science in Foreign Service from Georgetown University School of Foreign Service and is married with two sons.